Class Music_Sever

java.lang.Object
  Music_Sever

public class Music_Sever
extends Object

The Music_Sever class is responsible for maintaining a list of peers and thier songs. It is also responsible for providing clients with a address to connect to when they request songs.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Rhys Hill

Music_Sever

public Music_Sever()
The constructor for the Music_sever class. Sets up the peer list as a new Array List and then sets fileName to the text file used to store peers. This is always the same which is why is can be set here. It then updates the peer list based on its file.

peerOnline

public String peerOnline(String currentPeerName,
                         String address)
Checks if a peer is already know and if so sets them thier online to true. If not it gives them a new name, adds it to the peer list. Then returns the name and listening port for that peer.

Parameters:
currentPeerName - The suggested name of a peer. If it is unnamed this function will make a name
Returns:
String A true false value to represent whether or not that peer name is listed

updatePeerListFile

public void updatePeerListFile()
Reads form file the list of peers that the server knows about and adds them to it's array list which is used to keep track of peers through the program. Also establishes a connection to, or creates if it's not present, the peer list text file.
